article.headline: Santa Clara 69, Fresno State 64
article.story: SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) -- Kyle Bailey scored 18 of his game-high 21 points in the second half to lead Santa Clara to a 69-64 victory over Fresno State on Saturday night. Bailey's three-point shot with 6:23 remaining put Santa Clara ahead 54-53, and the Broncos led the rest of the way. Bailey also had eight rebounds and eight assists. Ethan Rohde scored 14 points for Santa Clara (2-2), and Travis Niesen added 13. Fresno State (0-2) had five players in double figures, led by Shantay Legans with 12. Mustafa Al-Sayyad and Renaldo Major each scored 12 points for the Bulldogs, while Marcus West and Francis Koffi added 10 apiece. Fresno State scored the last six points of the first half, but still trailed 26-25 at the break. The Bulldogs led by as many as five in the second half, at 36-31 with 16:13 left in the game, but they could never shake Santa Clara. Al Sayyad had a game-high 11 rebounds. Niesen led Santa Clara with nine. Both teams shot poorly in the first half, but both improved to 52 percent in the second half.
